				<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align: left;">
					<em style="">CLUST</em><span style="">ering 16S NGS sequences by&nbsp;</span><em style="">O</em><span style="">verlap&nbsp;</span><em style="">M</em><span
						style=""
					>inimization</span><br />
				</h2>

				<div>
					<div style="height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;"></div>
					<hr class="styled-hr" style="width: 100%;"></hr>
					<div style="height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;"></div>
				</div>

				<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align: left;">What is CLUSTOM-CLOUD?&nbsp;</h2>

				<div class="paragraph" style="text-align: left;">
					A CLUSTOM-CLOUD is the distributed 16S sequence-clustering program based on In-Memory Data Grid(IMDG) technology â€“ a distributed data structure to store an entire data in the main memory of multiple computing nodes. The CLUSTOM-CLOUD is able to rapidly cluster extremely large amounts of sequence data with high accuracy. Furthermore, it is designed for platform independence and ease of use without any complicated installation step. As like CLUSTOM(for details, see original <a
						href="http://www.plosone.org/article/info%3Adoi%2F10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0062623" title=""
					>CLUSTOM</a> paper), CLUSTOM-CLOUD also accepts a FASTA file of 16S sequences as input, validates the input format, assigns them to OTUs, and outputs a couple of files that represent: (i) sequences per OTU; (ii) the representative sequences of OTUs (refined seeds); and (iii) the number of sequences per OTU.
					<br />
				</div>

				<div>
					<div class="wsite-multicol">
						<div class="wsite-multicol-table-wrap" style="margin: 0 -15px;">
							<table class="wsite-multicol-table">
								<tbody class="wsite-multicol-tbody">
									<tr class="wsite-multicol-tr">
										<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width: 33.333333333333%; padding: 0 15px;">



											<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align: left;">
												<font size="4"><strong>Platform Independent</strong></font>
											</h2>

											<div class="paragraph" style="text-align: left;">
												<span style="">CLUSTOM-CLOUD, which is written in java language, is platform independent, and supports various computing
													environments without any complicated installation.</span><br /> <span style=""></span><br /> <span style=""></span><span style=""></span><br />
												<span style=""></span>
											</div>



										</td>
										<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width: 33.333333333333%; padding: 0 15px;">



											<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align: left;">
												<font size="4"><strong>Scalability and InMemoryDataGrid</strong></font>
											</h2>

											<div class="paragraph" style="text-align: left;">
												CLUSTOM-CLOUD is high availability and scalability sequence clustering program based on In-Memory Data Grid (IMDG). <span
													style="text-align: justify;"
												>By using the IMDG technique, CLUSTOM-CLOUD is capable of rapidly clustering the vast amount of sequence data.</span><br /> <span style=""></span>
											</div>



										</td>
										<td class="wsite-multicol-col" style="width: 33.333333333333%; padding: 0 15px;">



											<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align: left;">
												<strong><font size="4">Easy to use</font></strong>
											</h2>

											<div class="paragraph" style="text-align: left;">Just all you need to set the single xml and configuration files for CLUSTOM CLOUD.
												Please take a look at the manual. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</div>



										</td>
									</tr>
								</tbody>
							</table>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align: left;">Download CLUSTOM-CLOUD</h2>

				<div class="paragraph" style="text-align: left;">
					14 October, 2015: Release 1.0.0 available (&nbsp;<a
						href="release/clustom_cloud.zip"  title=""
					>download</a> and <a href="docs/manual.pdf" title="">manual</a> )
						,&nbsp;Java version of CLUSTOM (<a href="http://clustom.kopri.re.kr/servlet/Download?dir=samples&file=CLUSTOM_JAVA.tar.gz">download</a>)
				
				<br /><br /> <strong style="line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><font size="4" >
				*&nbsp;The previous version of CLUSTOM that can be accessed at http://clustom.kopri.re.kr is not available any more. </font></strong><br />
				If you want to run CLUSTOM, please download and use the java version of CLUSTOM above. Nevertheless, If you still have difficulty in running CLUSTOM, just contact us (email: kmkim@kopri.re.kr or rbdls77@kopri.re.kr) so that we can run your sequence data.
				</div>

				<h2 class="wsite-content-title" style="text-align: left;">Paper&nbsp;</h2>

				<div class="paragraph" style="text-align: left;">
					<span style="">1. Oh J, Choi C-H, Park M-K, Kim BK, Hwang K, Lee S-H, et al. (2016)&nbsp;</span><strong style="line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><font
						size="4"
					>CLUSTOM-CLOUD:&nbsp; In-Memory Data Grid-Based Software for Clustering 16S rRNA Sequence Data in the Cloud Environment</font></strong><span
						style=""
					>.&nbsp;</span> PLoS ONE 11(3): e0151064(<a href="http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0151064">link</a>)<br /> <span style=""></span>
					<span style="">2. Hwang K, et al. (2013)&nbsp;</span><strong style="line-height: normal; text-align: justify;"><font
						size="4"
					>CLUSTOM:&nbsp; A Novel Method for Clustering 16S rRNA Next Generation Sequences by Overlap Minimization</font></strong><span
						style=""
					>.&nbsp;</span> PLoS ONE 8(5): e62623.(<a href="http://www.plosone.org/article/info%3Adoi%2F10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0062623">link</a>)<br /> <span style="">&nbsp;</span>					
				</div>
				
